<subSubSection id="C315D5DE9153FFEFE77CCB7B2B83A549" pageId="4" pageNumber="438" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BB086559153FFEFE77CCB7B2C2FA2B6" blockId="4.[777,1375,600,1023]" pageId="4" pageNumber="438">
<emphasis id="B97B5A479153FFEFE77CCB7B2CFBA207" bold="true" box="[782,938,600,629]" pageId="4" pageNumber="438">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0FFDD69153FFEFE7B1CB7B2C09A2EE" authority="J. E. Gray, 1838" authorityName="J. E. Gray" authorityYear="1838" class="Mammalia" family="Mormoopidae" genus="Pteronotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="davyi">Pteronotus davyi J. E. Gray, 1838</taxonomicName>
<materialsCitation id="3B678C089153FFEFE71ECBA02C2FA2B6" pageId="4" pageNumber="438">
“Trimidad [Island],” 
<collectingCountry id="F318C6C59153FFEFE0EECBA02C2BA2B6" name="Trinidad and Tobago" pageId="4" pageNumber="438">Trinidad and Tobago</collectingCountry>
.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB086559153FFEFE77BCBE92A0AA3C2" blockId="4.[777,1375,600,1023]" pageId="4" pageNumber="438">
J. D. Smith in 1972 recognized three subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0FFDD69153FFEFE7D6CBD52B5FA361" authorityName="J. E. Gray" authorityYear="1838" box="[932,1038,758,787]" class="Mammalia" family="Mormoopidae" genus="Pteronotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="davyi">P. davyi</taxonomicName>
: P. d. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0FFDD69153FFEFE01ACBD52BFDA361" authorityName="J. E. Gray" authorityYear="1838" box="[1128,1196,758,787]" class="Mammalia" family="Mormoopidae" genus="Pteronotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="davyi">davyi</taxonomicName>
, P. d. fulvus, and P. d. incae. Molecular and morphometric studies have shown that P. davy: represents a species complex, supporting elevation of fulvus to a distinct species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB086559153FFEFE762CA982B83A549" blockId="4.[777,1375,600,1023]" lastBlockId="4.[167,1377,1030,3116]" pageId="4" pageNumber="438">
Hence, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0FFDD69153FFEFE7FACA982CA9A3AA" authorityName="J. E. Gray" authorityYear="1838" box="[904,1016,955,984]" class="Mammalia" family="Mormoopidae" genus="Pteronotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" sensu="stricto" species="davyi">P davyi</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A248E73C9153FFEFE078CA982BEEA3AA" box="[1034,1215,955,984]" pageId="4" pageNumber="438" sensu="stricto">sensu stricto</taxonomicNameLabel>
occurs in coastal lowlands of 
<collectingCountry id="F318C6C59153FFEFE05ACAFD2BE8A38D" box="[1064,1209,990,1023]" name="Venezuela" pageId="4" pageNumber="438">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
and in the Lesser Antilles, and as an isolated population in 
<collectingCountry id="F318C6C59153FFEFE718CD252CFCA455" box="[874,941,1030,1063]" name="Peru" pageId="4" pageNumber="438">Peru</collectingCountry>
; its distribution might extend to 
<collectingCountry id="F318C6C59153FFEFE4A2CD0E2E08A43C" box="[208,345,1069,1102]" name="Colombia" pageId="4" pageNumber="438">Colombia</collectingCountry>
and northward to 
<collectingCountry id="F318C6C59153FFEFE61ECD0E2C51A43C" box="[620,768,1069,1102]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="4" pageNumber="438">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F318C6C59153FFEFE739CD0E2C8DA43C" box="[843,988,1069,1102]" name="Nicaragua" pageId="4" pageNumber="438">Nicaragua</collectingCountry>
, but phylogenetic status of these populations has not been assessed. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0FFDD69153FFEFE699CD772CEEA407" authorityName="J. E. Gray" authorityYear="1838" box="[747,959,1108,1141]" class="Mammalia" family="Mormoopidae" genus="Pteronotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="davyi">Pteronotus davyi</taxonomicName>
seems uncommon in Central America, and no extant populations are known in 
<collectingCountry id="F318C6C59153FFEFE714CDA72C89A4EF" box="[870,984,1156,1181]" name="Panama" pageId="4" pageNumber="438">Panama</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F318C6C59153FFEFE795CDA72B03A4EF" box="[999,1106,1156,1181]" name="Guyana" pageId="4" pageNumber="438">Guyana</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F318C6C59153FFEFE013CDA72BBBA4EF" box="[1121,1258,1156,1181]" name="Suriname" pageId="4" pageNumber="438">Suriname</collectingCountry>
, French 
<collectingCountry id="F318C6C59153FFEFE4DBCD8F2E44A4B7" box="[169,277,1196,1221]" name="Guyana" pageId="4" pageNumber="438">Guyana</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="F318C6C59153FFEFE51ACD8F2EEBA4B7" box="[360,442,1196,1221]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="438">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. Occurrence records in north-eastern 
<collectingCountry id="F318C6C59153FFEFE797CD8F2B65A4B7" box="[997,1076,1196,1221]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="438">Brazil</collectingCountry>
were erroneous and corresponded to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0FFDD69153FFEFE5EFCDE82D09A49E" baseAuthorityName="Natterer" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[413,600,1227,1260]" class="Mammalia" family="Mormoopidae" genus="Pteronotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gymnonotus">P. gymnonotus</taxonomicName>
. Fossil records of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0FFDD69153FFEFE727CDE82CECA49E" authorityName="J. E. Gray" authorityYear="1838" box="[853,957,1227,1260]" class="Mammalia" family="Mormoopidae" genus="Pteronotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="davyi">P. davyi</taxonomicName>
are reported from 
<collectingRegion id="49CB48B79153FFEFE0BDCDE82A4FA49E" box="[1231,1310,1227,1260]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="4" pageNumber="438">Bahia</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="49CB48B79153FFEFE4DBCDD12FA7A561" box="[169,246,1266,1299]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="4" pageNumber="438">Goias</collectingRegion>
in 
<collectingCountry id="F318C6C59153FFEFE558CDD12E28A561" box="[298,377,1266,1299]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="438">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F318C6C59153FFEFE5B7CDD12DC0A561" box="[453,657,1266,1299]" name="Tobago Island" pageId="4" pageNumber="438">Tobago Island</collectingCountry>
. Based on fossil records, its distribution was more extensive in the late Quaternary than it is today. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
